QUICK START

1) Download the package cross-dics.tar.gz and linguistic data.

2) Unpack cross-dics and do:
   $ gunzip cross-dics.tar.gz
   $ tar xvf cross-dics.tar
   $ cd cross-dics

3) Compile source files
   $ ant compile

4) Copy linguistic data into folder "dics"

   - Bilingual dictionary A-B:   apertium-bb-aa.bb-aa.dix
   - Bilingual dictionary B-C:   apertium-bb-cc.bb-cc.dix
   - Morphological dictionary A:  apertium-bb-aa.aa.dix
   - Morphological dictionary C:  apertium-bb-cc.cc.dix

   Please note that:

   - all dictionaries must be in the form:
	* apertium-xx-yy.xx-yy.dix (bilingual dictionaries)
	* apertium-xx-yy.xx.dix (morphological dictionaries)
   - the common language (B) must be in the left side, that is, dictionaries
     in the form B-A and B-C

5) Edit build.xml and indicate the set of dictionaries as follows:

	<property name="bil-AB"  value="apertium-bb-aa.bb-aa.dix" />
	<property name="bil-BC"  value="apertium-bb-cc.bb-cc.dix" />
	<property name="monol-A" value="apertium-bb-aa.aa.dix" />
	<property name="monol-C" value="apertium-bb-cc.cc.dix" />
	<property name="mod-AB"  value="-n" />
	<property name="mod-BC" value="-n" />
	
	Note:	use "-r" instead of "-n" if the dictionary has to be reversed.
		(apertium-aa-bb.aa-bb.dix to apertium-bb-aa.bb-aa.dix)

	Do "ant help" to know how to use the command line instead of editing
build.xml.

6) Use the tool:

   $ ant cross

7) Crossed dictionaries can be found in folder "dix". The tool will generate
the following files:

	Crossed dictionaries ("safe crosssing")
	- apertium-aa-cc.aa-cc-crossed.dix
	- apertium-aa-cc.aa-crossed.dix
	- apertium-aa-cc.cc-crossed.dix

	Speculations
	- apertium-aa-cc.aa-cc-crossed-specul.dix
	- apertium-aa-cc.aa-crossed-specul.dix
	- apertium-aa-cc.cc-crossed-specul.dix

	Consistent dictionaries (without not common entries)
	- apertium-bb-aa.bb-aa-consistent.dix
	- apertium-bb-aa.aa-consistent.dix
	- apertium-bb-cc.bb-cc-consistent.dix
	- apertium-bb-cc.cc-consistent.dix

	Dictionaries with not common entries
	- apertium-bb-aa.bb-aa-not-common.dix
	- apertium-bb-aa.aa-not-common.dix
	- apertium-bb-cc.bb-cc-not-common.dix
	- apertium-bb-cc.cc-not-common.dix

8) Have a look at the source file 'HowTo.java' in src/ to see an simple example
using this library.

	Do "ant howto" to run this demo.




